description:
This bug has been thoroughly described on StackOverflow: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/22478183/why-is-this-sparql-query-not-returning-any-results/22479192
In summary, in a query containing (notice different predicates and same objects):
OPTIONAL { ?person dbpprop:workInstitution ?institution . }
OPTIONAL { ?person dbpprop:workInstitutions ?institution .}
FILTER(BOUND(?institution))

the variable ?institution is always evaluated as unbound even though always exactly one of the patterns matches and the other one does not.
It can be tested with the following query on DbPedia:
select ?person ?field ?institution where
{
  ?person a dbpedia-owl:Agent .
  OPTIONAL { ?person dbpprop:workInstitution ?institution . }
  OPTIONAL { ?person dbpprop:workInstitutions ?institution .}
  ?person dbpprop:field ?field .
  FILTER(BOUND(?institution))
}

